on 7/10/02 12:26 PM, Robert Mead at r.mead(-at-)att.net wrote:

> Can anyone tell me how to remove the horn button. I thought I'd ask
> first, rather than destroy it and thereby learn how not to remove it.

It's only held in by an attached metal clip going most of the way around.
Get a flat item in there, like a feeler gauge or finger nail and work your
way around until it pops off.

